This paper deals with location privacy-preserving mechanisms, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning models to learn users' behavior, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper proposes a new family of location privacy-preserving mechanisms, which involves designing algorithms and systems (cs.SI) and considering the impact on user privacy (cs.CY).
